videos.description: Virginia Tech freshman Nickeil Alexander-Walker grabs a defensive rebound and goes coast-to-coast, finishing with a high-arcing finger roll over his defender.
videos.headline: VT's Alexander-Walker scores with sweet finger roll

videos.description: Hokies forward Chris Clarke does it all, snaring a rebound and taking it the other way to score with a contested runner through contact.
videos.headline: Clarke goes coast-to-coast for and-1 bucket

videos.description: Chris Clarke kicks the ball out to Justin Bibbs who drains a contested 3-pointer to give Virginia Tech a 34-21 lead at halftime.
videos.headline: Hokies' Bibbs connects from downtown

videos.description: Virginia Tech head coach Buzz Williams praises his team's execution on defense, saying the Hokies did a nice job of forcing Notre Dame into tough shots.
videos.headline: Williams pleased with VT's 1st-half effort

videos.description: Hokies guard Justin Robinson contributes all over the floor, poking the ball loose on defense and dishing to Justin Bibbs for an easy transition score.
videos.headline: VT's Robinson steals and deals

videos.description: Virginia Tech breaks Notre Dame's zone, as Kerry Blackshear Jr. gets the ball under the rim and contorts around two defenders for the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: Hokies' Blackshear sinks acrobatic lay-in

videos.description: Despite his struggles from the field, Notre Dame's Bonzie Colson doesn't hesitate to shoot from deep and connects for his first 3 of the ACC Tournament.
videos.headline: Colson breaks out of slump with triple

videos.description: After trailing by as many as 21 points in the second half, Notre Dame cuts the deficit to four after Rex Pflueger sinks his shot from deep.
videos.headline: Notre Dame's Pflueger hits 3-ball to tighten game

videos.description: Bonzie Colson banks in a clutch 3-pointer in traffic to give Notre Dame the lead after trailing by as many as 21 in the second half.
videos.headline: Colson gives ND lead with contested triple

videos.description: Notre Dame forward Bonzie Colson says the Fighting Irish were able to overcome a 21-point second-half deficit because the team refused to give up.
videos.headline: Colson: Notre Dame 'fought' for comeback win
